---

I learned to watch for the echo chamber. AI tends to confirm existing ideas in an effort to please. It's sycophantic by default.

I actively steer it toward challenge mode: "What's wrong with this argument? What am I not seeing?" I push it to find where my reasoning breaks. I reject most of what it offers and redirect until the conversation surfaces something genuinely useful.

Without actively steering against confirmation, AI amplifies my existing biases rather than challenging them.
